{
  "texts": [
    "The architecture is grounded in an encoder-decoder framework, where each channel of the input RGB image is processed through distinct feature extraction blocks.",
    "These blocks feed into a newly developed spatio-spectral attention block composed of parallel spatial and spectral Multi-Self-Attention (MSA) units.",
    "These units concurrently process and integrate spatial and spectral data to promote enhanced cross-dimensional interactions.",
    "The subsequent spectrum-fusion attention module strategically synthesizes correlations among the tripartite representations derived from the spatio-spectral attention block, culminating in the reconstructed hyperspectral image output.",
    "The loss function used to train the model can be computed using Eq. 18."
  ]
}